Description:
Unbeatable Ocean Views from 110 Glorious Acres
Set high on the hill overlooking 110 glorious pastoral acres (approx), this partially renovated 3-bedroom brick veneer home boasts breathtaking ocean views over Swan Bay and Queenscliff to the Mornington Peninsula and beyond. With a sweeping aspect of Port Phillip Bay in its entirety, you can sit back in utter relaxation and ponder a life of tranquility as the ships go by.
The residence features new carpeting in a spacious living room with water views; new tiling in the air-conditioned kitchen and meals area; three oversized bedrooms with built-in robes; a large family room; a tiled bathroom, separate toilet and a laundry. Perfectly comfortable in its present state, there is also potential for further renovation or a complete redevelopment to create your own dream home (STCA).
Also featuring a garage with internal access and multiple sheds for machinery and livestock, this incredible property offers a peaceful and private lifestyle in a truly magnificent location. Arrange an inspection today - and prepare to be amazed.
Land: 110 acres approx.

Description:
Acreage with the Lot
This substantial family home on an acre at Drysdale has all the ingredients for self-sufficient, energy-efficient living: established vegetable garden beds, a vineyard, orchard, chicken run, plus five water tanks, 2kw solar power and energy-saving features throughout the home.
A circular driveway accesses the triple garage with remote controlled doors and rear roller door access. The shady verandah provides welcomes guests to this beautifully maintained home.
Growing families will revel in the space of separate living areas, three or four bedrooms (including large master with walk-in robe), two bathrooms and a library or study area. The large open plan formal lounge and dining feature a handy opening to the kitchen while the informal family area opens up to the outdoor living area, for more casual entertaining.
The timber kitchen has plenty of bench and cupboard space, with stainless steel oven, hotplates, rangehood and dishwasher, plus views of the outdoor entertaining area as well as the dining areas. Just off the family area is a large room currently used as a home office, but could easily serve as a fourth bedroom. An additional study area or library is found just off the entry.
Outdoor entertaining is truly a delight, with a large cabana providing year-round cover, complete with a built-in barbecue, fridge recess and even a separate toilet.
Other features include roller shutters, rice hull floor tiling, low voltage flourescent downlights, gas ducted heating, air-conditioner and good storage throughout. There's also a large two-room shed, with space for a caravan or boat on one side, while the other is fully insulated and wired, making it perfect for a gym, studio or rumpus room.
With so much to offer at such an affordable price, families in search of a lifestyle change must arrange an inspection.
Land: 4,006 sq m approx.

Description:
Contemporary Country Living
Designed and built by the current owners with eco technologies in mind, this stunning contemporary home blends beautifully into its rural environment. Surrounded by the ultimate low maintenance, yet lush, native gardens, the walls of north facing glass rising from the naturally undulating acre of land capture the best of the weather. The deliberate passive solar design fills the home with light and warmth.
From these windows, the 2 living rooms and kitchen/dining area all take advantage of the views across open fields and farmland. Both the master bedroom and fourth bedroom, at opposite ends of the home, open through sliding glass doors onto private decks overlooking the same view. The master also features ample walk-through robes and a modern ensuite while the fourth has a walk-through robe of its own and is situated directly beside the luxuriously designed bathroom. 2 additional bedrooms of generous proportions with oversized built-in robes complete the home.
Outside, the rendered structure of both the home and the first of 2 double garages are finished in neutral tones and a covered portico extends between them, beside which lies the secluded rear garden and vegie patch. The vegetables are fed from a 5,000 litre water tank with pump system that is tucked from view behind the second double colourbond garage, that also has space for a workshop and is fully concreted and powered, further down the property.
Overall, the feel of the home is one of comfort but with decadent touches that make it truly special. A real bonus is that this lovely country home is only a short walk to the Drysdale village shopping centre and restaurants.
Terms 10% deposit, balance 30/60/90/120 days
Land: 4,011 sq m approx.

Newly updated open plan kitchen with all the mod cons including S/S appliances & hidden cabinet fridge, guides through to family meals area with A/C, leading to expansive backyard offering room to move. So many options for outdoor entertainment - a veranda enclosed with Cafe blinds, paved courtyard area with shade sail, creek with own fairy-tale bridge, as well as multiple storage/hobby sheds. Looking for the country lifestyle in a practical location? This is a must see!

Description:
Magnificent Family Home with Pool
Positioned in a quiet court location, this well designed home is set amongst a low maintenance native garden with its manicured lawns and solar heated in ground pool; creating a private oasis for all the family to enjoy.
Beautifully presented this home features 4 bedrooms plus a large purpose built hobby room and separate walk in storeroom. The zoned living includes an elegant formal lounge and a spacious family room that leads through wide doors to the north facing outside entertaining area, adjacent the enticing pool.
Other features include large double garage with room for a workbench or gym, new quality appliances in the kitchen, established citrus trees, raised vegetable garden bed and trailer access to rear yard. All this just a short walk to Drysdale Primary School, Christian Colle ge Bellarine and the central township amenities.
This is certainly a most desirable property which will satisfy the most discerning buyer.

Description:
Magnificent Family Homestead in Garden Paradise
Beautifully positioned in a quiet court offering country-style living with town convenience, this magnificent brick homestead is privately set amongst landscaped gardens and manicured lawns to create an idyllic paradise that is nothing short of perfection.
Immaculately presented inside and out, the home features up to 6 bedrooms including a front-situated main with window seat, walk-in robe and ensuite, and multiple living areas including an elegant formal lounge with gas log fire, a spacious family living space and an enormous billiards room with vaulted timber ceiling, split-system air conditioner, built-in bar and adjoining bathroom. A big rear deck overlooks the enticing in-ground pool and lovely gardens.
There's a superb timber kitchen with stainless steel appliances and walk-in pantry; four bedrooms to the rear with built-in robes and ceiling fans; a study or 6th bedroom; a sunny, air-conditioned rumpus area; 3rd bathroom and a huge laundry. With ducted heating and cooling, top-quality fixtures and furnishings, a double auto garage with internal access and a big machinery shed/garage, this property is certain to captivate all who view it.
Land: 1511 sq m approx.

Description:
Perfect Rural Haven
In a prized semi-rural pocket of Drysdale where space and serenity are valued above all, this newly-released allotment of one acre (approx) provides the perfect setting for a brand-new home of real character (STCA). Set amongst quality established homes in a peaceful and private court, the potential on offer here will have potential buyers salivating.
Just a short stroll from shops and schools, yet retaining a tranquil pastoral air, this prime position is within close proximity of the Bellarine Peninsula's many wondrous attractions. Only 20 minutes from Geelong, 10 minutes from Ocean Grove and 5 from Portarlington, this rural haven offers easy access to coastal treats as well as city temptations.
With the Bellarine's fabulous beaches, vineyards and family activities at your door, the list of local attractions is virtually endless. Do not miss this incredible opportunity!

Description:
“Somerfield” on over 1000m2
Just a stones throw from the Historic Drysdale Train Station and walking distance to local schools, shops and the Rail Trail, this English inspired cottage is nestled behind a story book painted picket fence & manicured garden. Comprising 3BR with BIR master with WIR & ensuite, 3 living areas incl formal dining and timber kitchen with Butler’s pantry. The features incl study with built in bookshelves, large rumpus area looking over the beautifully landscaped gardens, with outdoor undercover living, in ground solar heated pool & 2 sheds both with power. Backing onto vacant rural land overlooking McLeod’s water holes, with rear access via Carriage Crescent, this home ticks all the boxes!

Potential Plus on an Acre of Possibilities!
With an elevated aspect providing views over Corio Bay, this 3-bedroom brick home on an allotment of approximately one acre presents a wonderful chance for you to secure your dream property. In peaceful, pastoral surroundings and with extraordinary scope for renovation, or redevelopment (STCA), the potential on offer here will set your imagination racing.
Perfectly positioned between Drysdale and Portarlington, just 25 minutes from Geelong and 15 minutes from Ocean Grove, this rural haven offers easy access to coastal treats as well as city temptations. With the Bellarine's fabulous beaches, vineyards and family activities at your door, the list of local attractions is virtually endless.
In fine condition throughout, the home itself comprises a spacious living room with water views, electric heater and air-conditioner; 3 bedrooms with robes, one with air conditioner and ceiling fan; a good kitchen/meals area; laundry, and central bathroom. With original floorboards and water tanks, this property will impress. Do not miss this incredible opportunity!

Description:
Immaculate Family Home is Certain to Impress
Just 6 years old and in immaculate condition throughout, this beautifully crafted two-storey home provides exceptional family living in a quiet, convenient location. Set on a large allotment amongst stunning established gardens with lovely white roses and a garden arch, this brilliant residence boasts instant street appeal, which only increases as you step inside.
Enter from the north-facing timber verandah to find gleaming polished floorboards; a spacious formal lounge; a carpeted family room, home office or extra bedroom; laundry with powder room; and a superb kitchen with stainless steel appliances serving a dining room with fernery window and doors to a sensational pergola area overlooking the large rear yard and gardens.
Upstairs you'll find four carpeted bedrooms with robes - the main with walk-in robe, ensuite and northern balcony - plus a family bathroom. With ducted heating, evaporative cooling, an oversize double garage with rear access and more, this truly spectacular home is just waiting for a new family to call it their own.

Description:
Ease of Living with Captivating Views
Ease of Living with Captivating Views
Exceptional rural lifestyle holding of 19 ha - 47.5 acres approx with uninterrupted panoramic views to Port Philip Bay,
Mt. Eliza and the Heads.
Quality three bedroom Architect Designed home incorporating two living areas with floor-to-ceiling windows to capture the magnificent views, a superb central kitchen with double oven and dishwasher and a spacious laundry with expansive cupboards. There are built in robes in all bedrooms plus an ensuite to the main and a paved pergola off the living areas.
The 5-plus acres vineyard established in 1979 is the earliest planted on the Bellarine Peninsula and consists of drip irrigated pinot noir and chardonnay vines. Grapes have been supplied to Scotchmans Hill's premium wines for over twenty years.
Complete with in-ground solar heated swimming pool, full-size tennis court, two dams and a shed.
Just five minutes to the Bayside town of Drysdale, 15 minutes to Ocean Grove and Surf beaches. 20 minutes to Geelong and just over an hour to Melbourne.
Suitable for a wide range of agricultural pursuits.
